     3в†’## Getting Started
     5в†’First, run the development server:
     6в†’
     7в†’```bash
     8в†’npm run dev
     9в†’# or
    10в†’yarn dev
    11в†’# or
    12в†’pnpm dev
    13в†’```
    14в†’
    15в†’Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) with your browser to see the result.
    16в†’
    17в†’You can start editing the page by modifying `app/page.tsx`. The page auto-updates as you edit the file.
    18в†’
    19в†’[API routes](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-routes/introduction) can be accessed on [http://localhost:3000/api/hello](http://localhost:3000/api/hello). This endpoint can be edited in `pages/api/hello.ts`.
    20в†’
    21в†’The `pages/api` directory is mapped to `/api/*`. Files in this directory are treated as [API routes](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-routes/introduction) instead of React pages.
    22в†’
    23в†’This project uses [`next/font`](https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/font-optimization) to automatically optimize and load Inter, a custom Google Font.
    24в†’
    25в†’## Learn More
    27в†’To learn more about Next.js, take a look at the following resources:
    28в†’
    29в†’- [Next.js Documentation](https://nextjs.org/docs) - learn about Next.js features and API.
    30в†’- [Learn Next.js](https://nextjs.org/learn) - an interactive Next.js tutorial.
    31в†’
    32в†’You can check out [the Next.js GitHub repository](https://github.com/vercel/next.js/) - your feedback and contributions are welcome!
    33в†’
    34в†’## Deploy on Vercel
    36в†’The easiest way to deploy your Next.js app is to use the [Vercel Platform](https://vercel.com/new?utm_medium=default-template&filter=next.js&utm_source=create-next-app&utm_campaign=create-next-app-readme) from the creators of Next.js.
    37в†’
    38в†’Check out our [Next.js deployment documentation](https://nextjs.org/docs/deployment) for more details.
